titleproper.value: Guide to the Robert C. Winthrop collection <num>1974.052</num>

creation.value: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace <date>2018-11-16T17:20:04</date>

extent.value: in seven folders in one manuscript box and one oversize folder.

abstract.value: This collection documents early Colonial property transactions in the Long Island towns of Brookhaven and Southold. Materials include, deeds, indetures, patents and warrents, and involve the Unkechaug Native Americans and English colonial administrator Edmund Andros.

p.value: Identification of item, date (if known); Robert C. Winthrop collection, 1974.052, Box and Folder number; Brooklyn Historical Society.
